abstract: Hollywood stars are making their way to Iowa and South Carolina. Will they change anyone’s mind?
snippet: Hollywood stars are making their way to Iowa and South Carolina. Will they change anyone’s mind?
lead_paragraph: SUMTER, S.C. — Bernice Harris was with her granddaughter Saturday afternoon when they heard a surprising rumor: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont was going to visit their city later that day, holding a rally at an African Methodist Episcopal Church.

headline_print_headline: Glittering Proxies Lend 2020 Democrats a Hand

abstract: The sudden breach between the two leading liberals in the Democratic primary race has disheartened those who fear it could provide an advantage to the party’s moderate candidates.
snippet: The sudden breach between the two leading liberals in the Democratic primary race has disheartened those who fear it could provide an advantage to the party’s moderate candidates.
lead_paragraph: Following Monday’s acrimonious exchanges between Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren, the leader of one left-wing activist group summed up the sudden breach between the two liberal presidential candidates with an analogy on Twitter: “Mom and dad are fighting and all I wanna do is go to my room and put my headphones on.”

headline_main: ‘Mom and Dad Are Fighting’: Left-Wing Democrats Lament Sanders-Warren Rift
headline_print_headline: Inside Clash Over a Disputed Remark on the Electability of Women
byline_original: By Astead W. Herndon and Shane Goldmacher

abstract: Bernie is surging and may have found his moment.
snippet: Bernie is surging and may have found his moment.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Hi, Gail. I’ve been coming around to the view that Bernie Sanders could really win the Democratic nomination and the presidency, and the numbers show it. A poll released last week by The Des Moines Register and CNN gives him the lead in Iowa, and he’s in strong contention for New Hampshire. His fund-raising is just extraordinary: more than $34 million last quarter, raised mostly in very small donations.

abstract: The caucuses were supposed to be less important this time. But they still might pick the winner.
snippet: The caucuses were supposed to be less important this time. But they still might pick the winner.
lead_paragraph: With Cory Booker’s exit, the Democratic field has lost another minority candidate, and revived the arguments — pressed by Julián Castro before his own exit from the race — that the whiteness of the Iowa electorate explains the increasing whiteness of the Democratic field.

abstract: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
snippet: We don’t care about Biden’s electability. We want excitement.
lead_paragraph: KNOXVILLE, Iowa — Welcome to the final Democratic debate before the Iowa caucuses. As a reporter for a small-town Iowa radio station, I have the best seat in the house for the caucuses. I’ve seen all the candidates who have come to Iowa, most multiple times, interviewed nearly all of them, some more than once, and attended countless events. The largest, the Polk County Steak Fry in September, had over 12,000 attendees. The smallest was, um, about 10 people about a week or two ago (sorry, Marianne Williamson!).

abstract: The New Jersey senator, who built his campaign around a message of unity, was unable to catch on with substantial numbers of voters and ended his quest before voting began.
snippet: The New Jersey senator, who built his campaign around a message of unity, was unable to catch on with substantial numbers of voters and ended his quest before voting began.
lead_paragraph: For almost two decades, Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey has been viewed as a future leader in the Democratic Party, a former Rhodes scholar and Stanford football player who achieved national prominence as mayor of Newark.

headline_main: Bernie Sanders Wants to Change Your Mind

abstract: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
snippet: Mr. Sanders edged out his competitors in The Des Moines Register/CNN poll released on Friday, the first significant survey from Iowa in nearly two months.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Bernie Sanders edged ahead of his Democratic rivals in Iowa, affirming his resurgence less than four weeks before next month’s caucuses, according to a new poll from The Des Moines Register and CNN.
